text: Nor Azli Yusoff was a Singaporean footballer who played as a midfielder in the Sleague. As of mid-year 2020, he remains a free agent and is currently not playing for any club. At 37 years old, there is the possibility of his retiring as an active player and there is some talk of his possible move into coaching. == Career == He started his career with the Cheetahs before moving to the Protectors.http://hufc.sg/news/an-interview-with-nor-azli-yusoff After his contract ended with Home United, he move to the Eagles in 2015 and stay on till now. ==Honours== ===Club=== Home United *Singapore Cup: 2013 *S.League: 2013 Runners Up Tanjong Pagar *Singapore League Cup: 2014 Runners Up == Career statistics == {| class="wikitable" style="text-align:center" |- !rowspan=2 width=160|Club !rowspan=2|Season !colspan=2|S.League !colspan=2|Singapore Cup !colspan=2|Singapore League Cup !colspan=2|Total |- !width=40|Apps!!width=40|Goals !width=40|Apps!!width=40|Goals !width=40|Apps!!width=40|Goals !width=40|Apps!!width=40|Goals |- |rowspan=2|Hougang United |2009 |18||0||0||0||0||0||0||0 |- |2010 |26||0||1||0||3||0||27||0 |- |rowspan=3|Home United |2011 |19||0||5||0||3||0||27||0 |- |2012 |20||0||3||0||3||0||26||0 |- |2013 |17||0||1||0||2||0||20||0 |- |Tanjong Pagar United |2014 |19||0||2||0||5||0||26||0 |- |rowspan=3|Geylang International |2015 |23||0||3||0||4||0||30||0 |- |2016 |17||0||3||0||4||0||24||0 |- |2017 |0||0||0||0||0||0||0||0 |- !colspan=2|Total !159!!0!!18!!0!!24!!0!!180!!0 |- !colspan=2|Career total !159!!0!!18!!0!!24!!0!!180!!0 |- |} == References == Category:1983 births Category:Living people Category:Singaporean footballers Category:Association football goalkeepers Category:Singapore Premier League players Category:Hougang United FC players Category:Home United FC players Category:Tanjong Pagar United FC players Category:Geylang International FC players
